{{hatnote|This article is about declarators under Scottish law. For other legal actions where one party might be known as the 'declarator', see [[Declaration (law)]].}}

A '''declarator''' in [[Scottish law]] is a form of [[legal action]] by which some [[legal right|right]] of [[property]], [[servitude in civil law|servitude]], or [[status (law)|status]] (or some other inferior right or interest) is sought to be [[declaration (law)|judicially declared]].<ref>{{cite EB1911|wstitle=Declarator |volume=7 |page=914}}</ref>


